^b@2The responder's bids will fall into one of three categories to help responder decide on the level and denomination of the final contract. 
These categories are essentially bidding messages to the opener.  
They are called  

- signoff, 
- invitational and 
- forcing bids.|
pg| ***** 2 ***** |


at|

1) A SIGNOFF bid is a response that asks the opener to pass.|
pg| ***** 3 ***** |


at|
2) An INVITATIONAL bid gives the opener the opportunity to pass or bid again.|
pg| ***** 4 ***** |


at|
3) A FORCING bid requires the opener to bid again.|
pg| ***** 5 ***** |


at|


You will learn more about how these three types of bids help you decide on the level and denomination of the final contract throughout the course. 
For now, just recognize that each bid sends a message.

