^b@2You saw that 2@c is not on that SIGNOFF bid list. 
This 2@c response to an opening bid of 1NT is reserved for a special purpose 
– the STAYMAN convention. 
We'll talk about that in our next lesson.
For now, you need to know that a 2@c response after a 1NT opening, has nothing to do with the club suit. 
(= artificial bid)
Therefore, you DO NOT respond 2@c with 0-8 points even if you know there is a Golden Fit in clubs. 
Instead you PASS and play 1NT|
