Let's take a look at the responder's strength category (3) 11-15 points
With 11-15 TP hands the partnership has 26-32 TP, enough for game.
If  responder knows that there is not Golden Fit in major suits (@h or @s), he just  bids 3NT  = SIGNOFF bid for opener.
If responder has a 6+ card in a major, he knows there is Golden Fit in that major and he bids 4@h or 4@s which is a  SIGNOFF bid for opener.
Our actual Responder 3 hand:  4@h = signoff, to play

REMINDER: Golden fit is 8+ cards in suit in combined hands. In this case 6 hearts in responder's hand and 2 as a minimum in Opener's 

Opener MUST pass on all 3 SIGNOFF bids!|
