^b@2Now very IMPORTANT!

If responder only has a 5-card Major, he wants to know, if partners has a 3 to 4 card support 
(he would want to play 4 of a major then), or if partner only has a 2-card in responder's major 
(in which case he would want to play in 3NT)

Therefore responder with 11-15 points uses the NATURAL FORCING bid at the 3 -level: 3@h or 3@s. 
Opener MUST bid ON.|
